column5: Awesome report! Can't wait for the drakes

Some very beautiful fish there. I spent all day doing the chuck and duck at logjams yesterday trying to catch some decent browns. Lost one about fifteen inches but that's all the luck I managed to have. Did watch a spent steelhead doing nose to tail rises at the tailout of a pool. Wish I would have had the proper filter that I could have caught it on video for everyone. I love wild leeks and  wild garlic.
Five great pics that told a perfect story.  And on top of that, you actually told a story.  Thanks.
Nice report & pics !!! Love the colors of those river browns !!!!! Looks like a nice spot too ...
You know how to spend a long weekend!  Love the wild edibles...how were the fiddleheads where you are?  I haven't seen any ripe for the pickin around here yet this year
sounds like an awesome trip and that brown trout is just beautiful. nice pictures, too...thanks!
Beautiful pictures, looks like a nice adventure!
jealous. looks like a great weekend for sure. need to catch me one of them browns.
The leaks look very similar to wild garlic...which I'll be eating tonight, along with fiddleheads and splake! Any tips on telling the difference other than smell/taste?
Nice report, great pics of some gorgeous lookin' brownies.
